      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:4:7:4",
      "text": [
        " مَا أَخَذَتِ الْحِبَالَةُ فَانْقَطَعَ مِنْهُ شَيْ‏ءٌ أَوْ مَاتَ فَهُوَ مَيْتَةٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Aban, from Abdullah Bin Suleyman, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘What the snare seizes, so something is cut off from it, or it dies, so it is dead’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. Aban has narrated from ‘Abd Allah ibn Sulayman who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Whatever of the prey is caught in the snare which is cut off or has died is dead.’” "
        ]
      }
